toDecimalPlaces

  • toDecimalPlaces(dp?, rm?): Decimal

  • Return a new Decimal whose value is the value of this Decimal rounded to a maximum of dp decimal places using rounding mode rm or rounding if rm is omitted.

    If dp is omitted, return a new Decimal whose value is the value of this Decimal.

    Parameters

    • Optional dp: number

      {number} Decimal places. Integer, 0 to MAX_DIGITS inclusive.

    • Optional rm: number

      {number} Rounding mode. Integer, 0 to 8 inclusive.

    Returns Decimal

    Inherited from Decimal.toDecimalPlaces

    • Defined in node_modules/decimal.js-light/decimal.d.ts:348

toFixed

  • toFixed(dp?, rm?): string

  • Return a string representing the value of this Decimal in normal (fixed-point) notation to dp fixed decimal places and rounded using rounding mode rm or rounding if rm is omitted.

    As with JavaScript numbers, (-0).toFixed(0) is '0', but e.g. (-0.00001).toFixed(0) is '-0'.

    Parameters

    • Optional dp: number

      {number} Decimal places. Integer, 0 to MAX_DIGITS inclusive.

    • Optional rm: number

      {number} Rounding mode. Integer, 0 to 8 inclusive.

      (-0).toFixed(0) is '0', but (-0.1).toFixed(0) is '-0'. (-0).toFixed(1) is '0.0', but (-0.01).toFixed(1) is '-0.0'. (-0).toFixed(3) is '0.000'. (-0.5).toFixed(0) is '-0'.

    Returns string

    Inherited from Decimal.toFixed

    • Defined in node_modules/decimal.js-light/decimal.d.ts:388
